olive oil
1 carrot
1 cucumber
½ lemon
1 packet ginger paste
1 tbs sesame oil
½ tbs soy sauce
½ tsp brown sugar
1 packet cornflour
1 tbs plain flour
1 bag Shredded Cabbage Mix
1 packet sweet chilli sauce
1 packet beef strips
1 bag coriander
1 packet garlic aioli
1 sachet Southeast Asian Spice Blend

• Grate the carrot.
• Thinly slice cucumber into half-moons.
• Slice lemon into wedges.
• Discard liquid from beef strip packaging.

• To a large heatproof bowl, add ginger paste.
• In a large frying pan, heat sesame oil over high heat until just smoking, 30 seconds. Remove from heat and carefully pour hot oil over ginger paste.
• Add the soy sauce, brown sugar and a good squeeze of lemon juice. Mix well and set aside.

• In a medium bowl, combine beef strips, Southeast Asian spice blend, a pinch of salt and a drizzle of olive oil.
• Add cornflour and the plain flour and toss beef to coat.
• Return the frying pan to high heat with a drizzle of olive oil. When oil is hot, cook beef strips in batches, tossing, until browned and cooked through, 1-2 minutes. Transfer to a paper towel-lined plate.


• Add garlic aioli to the dressing, along with shredded cabbage mix, carrot and cucumber. Toss to coat and season to taste.
• Divide creamy slaw between plates.
• Top with Thai-style beef and sweet chilli sauce.
• Tear over coriander to garnish. Serve with remaining lemon wedges. Enjoy!